Global notes:
Note (G1): PHOENIX models as follows:
      q = quasi-spherical
      r = r method
      s = spherical
Note (G3): Models as follows:
      PD = PHOENIX-DRIFT
      PC = PHOENIX-COND
       A = ATLAS
Note (G2): fitting coefficients:
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  (1)   Linear law       I({mu})/I(1) = 1-u(1-{mu})
  (2)   Quadratic law    I({mu})/I(1) = 1-a(1-{mu})-b(1-{mu})^2^
  (3)   Square root law  I({mu})/I(1) = 1-c(1-{mu})-d(1-sqrt({mu}))
  (4)   Logarithmic law  I({mu})/I(1) = 1-e(1-{mu})-f{mu}ln({mu})
  (5)   Exponential law  I({mu})/I(1) = 1-g(1-{mu})-h/[1-exp({mu})]
  (6)   Non-linear law   I({mu})/I(1) = 1 - a1*(1-{mu}^0.5^) - a2*(1-{mu})
                                          - a3*(1-{mu}^1.5^) - a4*(1-{mu}^2^)
  -------------------------------------------------------------------------
  where I(1) is the specific intensity at the center of the disk, u, a,
  b, c, d, e, f, a_i_ are the corresponding limb-darkening coefficients
  and {mu}=cos({gamma}), {gamma} being the angle between the line of
  sight and the emergent intensity
